Enterprise Application Architect· Singapore, Singapore
Enterprise Application Architect
Singapore, Singapore
Full Time Employment
Recruiter Comment: We are seeking for a candidate to join our client as an Enterprise Application Architect responsible for delivering major business solutions or participating on significant architecture initiatives. #Singapore #J2EE #Jobs
Share:Job DescriptionThe Enterprise Application Architect must be able to take high level direction, formulate a plan to achieve the goals and execute the plan. In addition, the Application Architect will be expected to be able to build consensus, resolve conflicts and mediate, when working on multiple tasks and initiatives concurrently.The candidate is expected to be strong in written, verbal and presentation communication skills and be able to collaborate effectively with senior enterprise architect peers, solution architects, as well as executive IT management and senior business leaders in the implementation of enterprise IT solutions.ResponsibilitiesWork and interface with Application Suite Owners, Division Heads, IT Teams and Business Units to elicit, capture and analyse business process driven application requirements, functional decomposition and business solution integration including defining naming and cataloguing standards and templates.Facilitate the communication of the re-designed business processes and functions as part of the business process change and solution implementation.Manage and evangelise a consistent approach for managing change to business processes and functions that drive the definition of application requirements, analysis and capture.Work with Subject Matter Experts (SMEs) to scope the level of detail of as-is application architecture, and identify gaps and improvement opportunities by modelling and analysing the options for the to-be application architecture.Develop expertise in application architecture modelling and provide training to IT teams on the process for defining application requirements, principles and models that align to business requirements.Manage and interface with other teams within the company to ensure that projects are managed systematically and in concert to meet business needs and not in silos.Define, develop, publish, manage and govern Enterprise Application Architecture repositories (including application maps, application architecture models, application interdependency maps etc. as well as the repository structure and content tools, standards, templates, processes and guidelines) to facilitate alignment of IT projects with each other and the over-arching goals of Group IT and the business.Ensure stakeholder (e.g. Application Suite Owners, Division Heads, IT Teams and Business Units) engagement, involvement, and satisfaction with projects and services delivered.RequirementsBachelor’s degree in IT or equivalent experiencesAt least 10 years of experience in enterprise solution specification, architecting, design and development rolesAt least 5 years of experience as an enterprise architect and / or senior solution architect / manager in 1 or more complete enterprise projects on the same architecture, preferably in the logistics or transportation domainExperience in full development lifecycle phasesExperience in designing enterprise software and defining Solution Architectures and technologyExperience in AGILE, SCRUM, TDA methodology would be an advantageExperience facilitating meetings with multiple customers and technical staff, including building consensus and mediating compromises when necessaryExperience in developing enterprise architecture principles, policies, standards, templates and processes and guiding and governing solution design and development teams by themExperience in establishing EA tool-repositories and integrating their use in enterprise solution development processesExperience in designing applications using relational databasesFamiliarity with various requirements gathering techniquesFamiliarity with configuration management concepts and toolsProven technical leadership in enterprise architecture and solution development and deploymentMust be able to communicate fluently in English, both written and verbalOverall understanding of the business objectives of service lines and core business services departmentsEnterprise Architecture development frameworks – The Open Group Architecture Framework (TOGAF) 8 or 9 preferredEnterprise Architecture policy, standards and processes drafting, review and implementationEnterprise Architecture tools and repositories – knowledge of Software AG ARIS platform and Embarcadero’s ER/Studio platform preferredService Oriented ArchitectureEvent Driven ArchitectureMicrosoft SQL, Oracle RDBMSJ2EEIBM WebSphere integration suite: Message Broker, WSRR, MQSI, WSPS, WSBM, Transformation Extender, Information Server, Tivoli ITCAM for SOAOracle WeblogicMQ, RMI, JMS and JCASAP XI/PI and NetWeaverPlease send your resume in WORD format to yvonne.tan@lysten.com.sg or contact Yvonne Tan on +65 6332 0138 for a confidential discussion. Please note that only short-listed candidates will be contacted.ProfileYour IT Trained Recruiter
